#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn46.53"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn46.53:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 46 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 46 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.53:0.2"
msgid "6. Sākacchavagga "
msgstr "6. Discussion "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn46.53:0.3"
msgid "53. Aggisutta "
msgstr "53. Fire "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.112, sc1
msgctxt "sn46.53:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pavisiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then several mendicants robed up in the morning and, taking their bowls and robes, entered Sāvatthī for alms. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.53:1.2"
msgid "(Pariyāyasuttasadisaṃ.) "
msgstr "(The same as the previous discourse.) "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn46.53:2.1"
msgid "“Evaṃvādino, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when wanderers who follow other paths say this, you should say to them: "

msgctxt "sn46.53:2.2"
msgid "‘yasmiṃ, āvuso, samaye līnaṃ cittaṃ hoti, katamesaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bojjhaṅgānaṃ akālo bhāvanāya, katamesaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bojjhaṅgānaṃ kālo bhāvanāya? "
msgstr "‘Reverends, which awakening factors should not be developed when the mind is sluggish? And which awakening factors should be developed at that time? "

msgctxt "sn46.53:2.3"
msgid "Yasmiṃ panāvuso, samaye uddhataṃ cittaṃ hoti, katamesaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bojjhaṅgānaṃ akālo bhāvanāya, katamesaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bojjhaṅgānaṃ kālo bhāvanāyā’ti? "
msgstr "Which awakening factors should not be developed when the mind is restless? And which awakening factors should be developed at that time?’ "

msgctxt "sn46.53:2.4"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhā, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā na ceva sampāyissanti, uttariñca vighātaṃ āpajjissanti. "
msgstr "Questioned like this, the wanderers who follow other paths would be stumped, and, in addition, would get frustrated. "

msgctxt "sn46.53:2.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn46.53:2.6"
msgid "Yathā taṃ, bhikkhave, avisayasmiṃ. "
msgstr "Because they’re out of their element. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn46.53:3.1"
msgid "Nāhaṃ taṃ, bhikkhave, passāmi sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya yo imesaṃ pañhānaṃ veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ ārādheyya, aññatra tathāgatena vā tathāgatasāvakena vā ito vā pana sutvā. "
msgstr "I don’t see anyone in this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—who could provide a satisfying answer to these questions except for the Realized One or his disciple or someone who has heard it from them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn46.53:4.1"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye līnaṃ cittaṃ hoti, akālo tasmiṃ samaye passaddhisambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya, akālo samādhisambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya, akālo upekkhāsambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya. "
msgstr "When the mind is sluggish, it’s the wrong time to develop the awakening factors of tranquility, immersion, and equanimity. "

msgctxt "sn46.53:4.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn46.53:4.3"
msgid "Līnaṃ, bhikkhave, cittaṃ taṃ etehi dhammehi dussamuṭṭhāpayaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Because it’s hard to stimulate a sluggish mind with these things. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.113, sc5
msgctxt "sn46.53:5.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso parittaṃ aggiṃ ujjāletukāmo assa. "
msgstr "Suppose someone wanted to make a small fire flare up. "

msgctxt "sn46.53:5.2"
msgid "So tattha allāni ceva tiṇāni pakkhipeyya, allāni ca gomayāni pakkhipeyya, allāni ca kaṭṭhāni pakkhipeyya, udakavātañca dadeyya, paṃsukena ca okireyya; "
msgstr "If they toss wet grass, cow-dung, and timber on it, spray it with water, and scatter dirt on it, "

msgctxt "sn46.53:5.3"
msgid "bhabbo nu kho so puriso parittaṃ aggiṃ ujjāletun”ti? "
msgstr "could they make it flare up?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.53:5.4"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn46.53:6.1"
msgid "“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yasmiṃ samaye līnaṃ cittaṃ hoti, akālo tasmiṃ samaye passaddhisambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya, akālo samādhisambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya, akālo upekkhāsambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya. "
msgstr "“In the same way, when the mind is sluggish, it’s the wrong time to develop the awakening factors of tranquility, immersion, and equanimity. "

